Discover the charm of Sam's Grill (@samsgrillsf), a historic San Francisco gem and one of America's oldest restaurants, featured in a @Forbes piece by Chelsea Davis (@cheycheyfromthebay). 🌁 ✨

Known for its fresh, locally sourced seafood and classic dishes served in an intimate setting with old-school curtain booths and formal service, Sam's Grill is more than a dining experience—it's a piece of history. If you've never had frog 🐸 or you're thinking ew — go to one Michelin starred @anglersanfrancisco & get your mind blown!

I checked out Angler's new Quick Catch lunch menu that offers 3 courses for $38 & tried some of their al la carte items.

While the $38 power lunch is a steal, especially on the Embarcadero, I recommend getting a few a la carte items, particularly the Hot Fried Frog Legs with Cardamom Crème Fraîche & the Angler potato! You won't regret spending the extra $$$.

🐟 Here's what we ate & will come back for!

• Hot Fried Frog Legs with Cardamom Crème Fraîche
• Kingfish Cru, Yuzu & Fig Leaf
• Pacific Oysters with Seaweed Vinegar and Embered Tomato
• Angler Potato with Sauce of Taleggio
• Lobster Buns
• Blistered Asparagus, Chili & Pistachio
• Sea Bream with Coconut & Swarnadwipa
• Soft Serve Sundae
• Coconut Sorbet

Would you try frog? Let me know in the comments below!

caption:
🎸INTRODUCING: JAMS ON JESSIE by @NoisePop!

🤘🏼This Thursday, May 2nd, Jessie Street comes alive with bands and live music brought to you by Noise Pop! 

🍄 @agoutiband is a psychedelic rock band that surfaced from songwriter and producer Carmen Caruso after a trip to Costa Rica’s cloud forests. Escaping from chronic fatigue and dysfunctional routine, she ruminated on what to do next. Caruso realized many of her musical facets - early experiences in choir, infatuation with 60s and 70s rock, forays into building new instruments, and making experimental music - all oscillated around psychedelic rock.

🌙 @mild_universe is a San Francisco based collective crafting dreamy dance music. Their recent singles are genre-bending, energetic dance anthems with simple, repetitive lyrics that are an homage to 90’s club music, with a disco-era instrumental feel. With an anticipated debut album on the horizon, Mild Universe aims to unite communities through music and movement.

⭐️Behind Oakland CA-based ensemble @OrchestraGold’s original sound is a decade-long story of knowledge,
respect, and collaboration between Mariam Diakite of Mali and Erich Huffaker of Oakland. Blending the traditions of Mali and American Rock/Funk with a retro feel, OG represents a world of powerful cross-cultural experience. The group transcends borders and boundaries to be a force of healing within the community. OG offers a kaleidoscope of magical sound deeply rooted in the past while boldly blazing towards the genre-bending future: African Psychedelic Rock.

caption:
I came to @berkeleyrep for the world-premiere of Galileo: A Rock Musical, and it is a must see! I took BART from the city to Downtown Berkeley and it was a short 1 minute walk from the station to the Berkeley Repertory Theatre. It’ll be here until June 23. This was my first time here, so we pre ordered some drinks and snacks to pick up when we arrived. I highly recommend getting their signature drink, it’s so pretty. Then, we walked into the theater to find our seats and the overall performance was dramatic, comedic, and just really fun to watch. The projections and stage props were incredible. The story follows a scientist who, against all odds, challenged humanity’s understanding of its place in the universe. The original rock score and lyrics, combined with such a star-studded cast and team really brought  this performance together. Definitely check out Berkeley Rep’s other two events programmed during the run of Galileo. They have a Musical Theatre Trivia night on May 9, and a Pride Night on June 7. You gotta check it out!

📍 2025 Addison St, Berkeley, CA 94704
#GalileoBRT #BerkeleyRep #sfinfluencer #sfblogger #funthingstodoinberkeley

caption:
@berkeleyrep just hosted the world-premiere of Galileo: A Rock Musical! We had such a fun time at this performance, so here’s everything you need to know:

This show runs from 5/5 - 6/23
Four-time Tony Award nominee Raúl Esparza stars in a dazzling world-premiere musical helmed by Tony Award winner Michael Mayer (Spring Awakening, American Idiot, Swept Away), written by two-time Emmy winner Danny Strong (Dopesick, Empire, The Butler). It features original rock score and lyrics by Michael Weiner (Broadway’s First Date) and Zoe Sarnak
(Jonathan Larson Award winner). 

Definitely come early before the show on these dates to catch these two events programmed during the run:

a. Musical Theatre Trivia Night: Join Berkeley Rep on May 9 in Michael’s Second Act bar for an epic Trivia Night celebrating Berkeley Rep’s dazzling new musical Galileo. Show off your musical theatre prowess, score awesome prizes, and mingle with fellow theatre lovers before the evening’s performance. Doors open at 6:30pm. This event is free and open to the public.

b. Pride Night: Join Berkeley Rep on June 7 in the Narsai M. David Courtyard for Cosmic Odyssey: A Pride Celebration. Hosted by Sir Joq, this special preshow will feature performances by Polly Amber Ross, Qozmo the Clown, Jota Mercury, and more! Light bites provided by Heroic Italian and wine provided by Perfusion Vineyard. Doors open at 6:45pm. This event is free and open to the public.

You gotta check it out!

alt: Photo shared by Andrew De Los Santos on May 07, 2024 tagging @thespeakeasysf, and @xandreats_. May be an image of 2 people, bowler hat, night and text.
caption:
@thespeakeasysf is the hottest immersive speakeasy and it’s back in San Francisco! I came with a friend to The Speakeasy SF, where we started by finding our contact on the street to get the secret passphrase to find the location. It’s here until June 23rd. It was pretty fun to dress up like we were in the 1920’s and join a plethora of other people excited to take a step into the Roaring 20’s. There are generally no photos or pictures allowed, but I got special permission to give you guys a sneak peak of what to expect. 

We got to experience a ton of unique storylines by actors that really embodied their characters and even involved some people in the crowd to play along. There are multiple rooms, like the Casino, where we played games like poker, blackjack, and even craps. Since it is a prohibition, there are many secret passages and hidden doors for you to explore, and themed cocktails you can order. 

For a nice keepsake, definitely look for their “Man in the Moon” photobooth to have your picture taken. We ended the night with a cabaret show, and it was phenomenal. The singing, drama, and overall performances were 10/10. You gotta check it out!

alt: Photo shared by Andrew De Los Santos on May 01, 2024 tagging @thebelvedere_sf. May be an image of 8 people.
caption:
@thebelvedere_sf is the newest luxury condo building in the Cow Hollow District in SF. I came to the grand opening of the Belvedere, and out of the 28 new 2 and 3-bedrooms condos, we got to explore 6 of them. 
*They now have 10 of 28 in contract or sold*

From the upper floors to the lower ones, I started by checking out this 3-bedroom on the 5th floor with a rear view. It was a model unit, and I just love the view of the golden gate bridge from the bedroom as well as this amazing balcony. Next, I saw a 2-bedroom on the 4th floor with a front view. This was an empty unit, but it really showed how massive the spaces are. The kitchen especially. And you have a nice view of Van ness. Moving on, I saw another one right next door for the same price. This was a model unit with a front view and I love this stand alone tub. 

Finally, I moved onto the third floor. This 2 bedroom was smallest of all the ones I saw, but I like how they staged the space and it has an amazing rear view from the balcony. The bedrooms are a bit smaller, but they do not compromise on bathroom space. Next, was a 2 and a half bedroom, which was the largest of all the 2 bedrooms I saw. It has a cute additional office area with a sliding door right off the kitchen. The bathroom has a longer configuration and there’s even a huge closet-like room in the back. Finally, we saw the last 2-bedroom on this floor and overall, these are all absolutely beautiful units, no matter which one you get. Definitely contact Belvedere to get a tour if you’re interested in buying. You gotta check it out!

*Note: Units 501, 302, and 303 have been sold*

📍2525 Van Ness Ave. San Francisco, CA 94103
#TheBelvedere #SanFranciscoRealEstate #LuxuryRealEstate #sfinfluencer #sfblogger

caption:
This is how I spent a sunny day in the bay. And it might be cheaper than you’d think. First, my friend and I took a @sanfranciscobayferry from the @ferrybuilding and believe it or not, this was cheaper than the cost of a latte. We arrived at @jacklondonsq at @visitoakland and walked over to @thaifarmhouse . I love their fun cocktails and you cannot beat this view. It’s so pretty inside and out. 

Afterwards, we took a Lyft to the @marinavillageyachtharbor in Alameda @loveourisland . This was a beautiful and sunny day. My friend booked one of the yachts for 2 hours through Yaachtly. The prices can range in the $200’s when docked, to over a thousand when cruising. They have a lot of different yachts you can choose from, so It really depends how large of a party you have and if you want to be cruising on the water or not. We just brought our own food and drinks, played some music on our speakers, and had a fun time. Definitely do some photo ops while you’re here. 

Afterwards, I went back to the city to end with a yoga class at @templesf_immersive . I usually come here to @temple_sf to go clubbing, so this felt like some alternate reality. They had some complimentary tea and snacks before it started. @savvyhealing led the class and it was like a mix of yoga, sound healing, and aroma therapy all at once. It was the perfect way to end my weekend. You gotta check it out!

alt: Photo shared by SF Social Club on January 10, 2024 tagging @margieajiang.
caption:
when I moved to San Francisco as a recent grad and young professional, I found it difficult to discover and navigate the communities and events I wanted to be part of in the city. this past year, I also struggled with finding community, meeting new people, and making new friends... I was no longer spending the majority of my days dancing with my closest friends and teammates, and most of my college friends had left SF for the East Coast or grad school. I had so many different interests and wanted to be part of something bigger, but didn’t know where to start and was overwhelmed by various sources of information online.

thus, I’m creating a new community and platform to better connect those of us in SF with the things we love to do and are interested in exploring — amplifying the communities that exist in the city, supporting and working together with local businesses, and spreading awareness of events. ✨ through this journey, I’ve already connected with many supportive, passionate, and inspiring people and have been learning more and more about the incredible communities and businesses doing exciting work in SF.

if this resonates with you, I’d love for you to join the vision and help build our ‘community of communities’! you can fill out the membership form linked in our bio (or just show us lots of love and support 🫶), and keep an eye out for more updates and events coming soon 🤍 looking forward to a great year ahead!

xoxo,
margie

caption:
I’ve been going to @topofthemarksf for years, and they just celebrated their 85th Anniversary. Top of the Mark at the @icmarkhopkins in Nob HIll was so kind to invite me to their celebration yesterday. Michael, the general manager told us the story of how hotel opened back in 1926, nearly a century ago. The main stage was historically known to host live bands, so I was so happy we got to experience some of that. Props to @vintagejukeboxmusic . We got some champagne, light bites, and even got to customize our own old fashioned. I got mine made with strawberry rhubard and peach bitters. If you come here on an empty stomach, they do also have some delicious options on their menu, my favorite being one of the flatbreads to start, short rib sliders for the main, and a chocolate lava cake for dessert. Definitely come during sunset to catch golden hour. You gotta check it out! 

📍 999 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108

caption:
San Francisco Hosts First Official Diwali Celebration With the 2024 Bhangra and Beats Night Market

4-Part Cultural Event Series in the Financial District Kicks Off May 10, 2024
.
.
We are thrilled to announce the first official Diwali celebration in the City and County of San Francisco as part of the highly anticipated return of the Bhangra and Beats Night Market series. 

Following the immense success of the inaugural series last year, four FREE night markets are set to light up Downtown SF on the following dates in 2024: May 10th (AAPI Heritage Month), July 12th (Afrobeat Month), and September 13th (Latin Heritage Month). The four-part series will culminate with the City and County of San Francisco’s Inaugural Diwali Celebration on November 15th. 

The Bhangra and Beats Night Market will once again transform three city blocks into a vibrant cultural nightlife destination and marketplace. The events will run from 5 pm to 10 pm, offering an immersive experience featuring the dynamic sound of South Asian Bhangra music and other popular Bay Area music genres showcased on two stages - The Bhangra and Beats and World Music Stage.

Attendees can indulge in delectable street food, sip on refreshing cocktails, and explore over 30 unique local artisans and retailers offering rare Indian goods, San Francisco-made jewelry, apparel, personal care products, and art.

Bhangra and Beats is presented by @intothestreetssf and @nonstopbhangra in partnership with @sfoewd @sfmayorsoffice
.
.
Media and community partners include Advance @sf_downtown @newdelhisf , @caamedia, @3rdifilms @106kmel , and @wild949 
.
.
RSVP’s now open for May 10th Season Kick Off! Link in profile! 
.

alt: Photo by Our Block 🧱 in The Korner Store Bites & Vibes with @thekornerstore_sf. May be an image of car and text that says 'OPEN @ THE KORNER DECKS. STORE Thursday May 9, ThursdayMay9,2024 2024 8 PM I 4516 Mission St'.
caption:
📣 📣 PSA!! We are now hosting Open Decks *twice* a month!!! 📣 📣
thank you all so much for making this event such a vibe, we had to make it twice as nice! stay tuned for the next one 😎

it’s like open mic, but for DJs. we’re taking over our favorite korean restaurant and bar yet AGAIN to host an open decks night like you’ve never experienced before 💥

we want to create spaces for DJs of all experience levels to be able to:
- share the music they love
- share their own music
- play in front of a live crowd
- connect with other like minded people
- get exposure to professional level equipment they might not have at home
ALL while having good food and drinks 💕

it’s also a space for people who just wanna have a good time and enjoy the art of DJing ✨

for the music enjoyers:
bring good vibes, make some new friends, eat some good food, drink some good drinks

for the DJs:
- bring your usb, make some new friends, eat some good food, drink some good drinks
- there are limited slots on a first come first serve basis so arrive early to claim your spot!!
- we’ll be using a pioneer xdj-xz, make sure your files are formatted for REKORDBOX!

caption:
Discover San Francisco's cultural gems for FREE this January 2024! 🌉🖼️ 

From the SF Botanical Garden to the de Young Museum, and SFMOMA to the Asian Art Museum, there's something for everyone.

Rally was hosting a cycling class at @crunchgym in Russian Hill, so I had to come support. It’s inside this old theatre and they actually play movies while you workout. How cool is that? He had a fun playlist during class along with lights that made me feel like I’m at the club. It was intense and we even did some workouts with weights towards the end. His energy is so contagious, I highly recommend checking out his class at Crunch Fitness. You gotta check it out! 

📍 2330 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109

caption:
@palacehotelsf is one of the most beautiful hotels I’ve ever stayed at in SF. And I’ve stayed at a lot of them. Bonus points for them hosting a  @vitaminstringquartet concert by @napafest that covered artists like Taylor Swift and Coldplay. Last weekend, I ended my birthday month @sf_downtown at the Palace Hotel and it is gorgeous. 

My friends and I started the festivities at the @piedpipersf , which is an elegant bar with a huge iconic painting by the artist, Maxfield Parrish. We got a couple of drinks, we love a nice Smokey old fashioned, before ordering some food. We got oysters with yuzu kosho, garlic truffle fries, this is always a must for me, and a charcuterie board. 

Then, we went to check out my suite. The staff surprised me me a cake, hand written card, and balloons. It was the perfect way for me to celebrate with friends while enjoying this staycation. I really loved the bathroom that came with luxury products from @officialbyredo along with a toilet with heated seats and a bidet. 

Next, we went to the Garden Court to watch the Vitamin String Quartet. I’ve been listening to them on Spotify for years. They played the most breathtaking songs, my favorite being some of the soundtrack from Bridgetton. It was beautiful. You can catch performances like this at Festival Napa Valley July 6-21. 

Afterwards, I went out for dinner and drinks with some friends before coming back to the Palace Hotel to enjoy the nighttime views. The follow morning, definitely make your way to their gym and pool. This is the first time I ever stayed at a hotel in SF with a pool and it’s pretty cool. Afterwards, grab some breakfast at the Garden Court. It’s so chill. You gotta check it out!

📍 2 New Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94105
#sfinfluencer #sffoodie #sfblogger #sfhotels #napafest

caption:
This is everything I did in @coachella Day 3. We started by fueling up at the @hiltonpalmsprings before taking the shuttle to the festival. We finally went into the @absolutvodka tent and it was like a house party with good AC. Then, we went to the Central Market to eat some vegan ceviche from @cenavegan , which I surprisingly liked. We cooled down at the Do Lab stage before reapplying sunscreen and  grabbing some Yerba Mate teas by @drinkerva . I finally got my boba and then we went to the Rose Garden. It’s a beautiful spot inside the VIP area that’s perfect for pictures. Afterwards, we watched @victoriamonet at the Mojave stage and she was such a fun performer. 

Next to this stage was the Quasar stage, where we met up with a friend or ours to watch @diplo . He kills it every time. On the way back to VIP, we stopped by the Living Room and it really felt like a party at a living room. Finally, we ended with @dojacat at the Coachella stage and she was outstanding. The fire, harmony, and dancers were 10/10. I had so much fun for my first time at Coachella . And that day was 3. 

#coachella #coachella2024 #coachellaweekend2

Based in the San Francisco Bay Area, bilingual Emcee/Rapper Deuce Eclipse and co-founder/vocalist of Bang Data, draws influence from both his Nicaraguan heritage as well as the culture of Hip-Hop he grew up with in the United States.

By age Nine, he began rapping with a middle school friend, the two adopting the names ‘Ace Moon’ and ‘Deuce Eclipse’, which he carries with respect to this day.

Since then, he has released a variety of albums and countless songs, some of which have been featured on many TV shows, commercials, and movies. Most recently his song ‘Listen’ on ABC’s show Grown-ish and most notably the song ‘Bang Data’ on AMC’s show Breaking Bad, as well as George Lopez’s movie Spare Parts.

caption:
@afterworkbarsf in SF serves @superduperburgers burgers and @thebirdsf fried chicken sandwiches!
If you’re looking for a sports bar in SF with good burgers, I got you. I came to Afterwork Bar in Hayes Valley coincidentally after work and it’s pretty chill. They have super duper burgers and fried chicken sandwiches from The Bird and they were just the perfect things to eat after a long day. Definitely pair them with a cocktail or even a pitcher of beer during happy hour. We also ordered their buffalo wings, fried cauliflower, and onion rings on the side. And you cannot skip out on their apple fritters for dessert. I have to come back for one of their themed nights like Karaoke Mondays, Loteria Tuesdays, or Trivia Wednesdays. You gotta check it out! 

📍 409 Gough St, San Francisco, CA 94102

alt: Photo shared by Andrew De Los Santos on April 25, 2024 tagging @sumaiyaf24, @sf_japantown, @andreweatsinsf, and @fermlabsf_japantown. May be an image of 6 people, drink, wine glass and silver oak tree.
caption:
How to spend a night out in @sf_japantown . We met up at @fermlabsf_japantown for dinner, which is a gorgeous restaurant that opened at the end of last year. They have a wine Wednesdays where if you get a bottle of this Korean wine @vasocellars , you can get some goodies on the side. We enjoyed the appetizers and then ordered some drinks. I swear they make the best cocktails in Japantown. We got the Cool as a Kyuuri with gin and cucumber, this was so refreshing, The Boss Lady, I like how this kinda tasted like cherries, and the passion totem which has a delicious passionfruit taste. Finally, came all the mains. We got the braised pork belly, this was so tender, uni pasta, which was made with squid ink for that dark look, and then another pasta with shrimp. One of the owners surprised us with a lychee martini with real lychee and you really don’t taste the alcohol. It was that good. 

Then, we made our way over to @amctheatres Kabuki to watch the advanced screening of @challengersmovie and if you like love triangles and tennis, it is a must watch. Finally, we ended with karaoke over at Dimples. We got some drinks, sang our heart out to Backstreet Boys, and that’s how we spent a night out in Japantown. 

📍 1700A Post St, San Francisco, CA 94115

caption:
My neighbor @ral.credeur hosted a class at @crunchpolkst and it was at such a unique spot that I had to post about it! Rally was hosting a cycling class at @crunchgym in Russian Hill, so I had to come support. It’s inside this old theatre and they actually play movies while you workout. How cool is that? He had a fun playlist during class along with lights that made me feel like I’m at the club. It was intense and we even did some workouts with weights towards the end. His energy is so contagious, I highly recommend checking out his class at Crunch Fitness. You gotta check it out! 

📍 2330 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109

alt: Photo by Our Block 🧱 in The Korner Store Bites & Vibes with @thekornerstore_sf.
caption:
we’re running it back with @thekornerstore_sf for another open decks!! come join us for bites, vibes, and drinks 🧃

✅ Make sure to tag your DJ Friends & let’s see what you got!
✅ Sign ups are in-person. First come first serve.
✅ We open at 6pm, so get here early if you wanna get down on the decks and some noms to fuel that bpm
✅ We’ll do our best to make sure everyone gets a shot to throw down some 🔥🔥
✅ Music starts at 9pm

You know the vibes!! It’s like open mic, but for DJs. We’re taking over our favorite korean restaurant and bar to host an open decks night like you’ve never experienced before

We want to create spaces for DJs of all experience levels to be able to:
- share the music they love
- share their own music
- play in front of a live crowd
- connect with other like minded people
- get exposure to professional level equipment they might not have at home
ALL while having good food and drinks 💕

It’s also a space for people who just wanna have a good time and enjoy the art of DJing ✨

For the DJs:
Bring your usb, make some new friends, eat some good food, drink some good drinks
🚨We’ll be using a Pioneer XDJ-XZ, make sure your files are formatted for REKORDBOX!🚨

caption:
How to spend a night out in @sf_japantown . We met up at @fermlabsf_japantown for dinner, which is a gorgeous restaurant that opened at the end of last year. They have a wine Wednesdays where if you get a bottle of this Korean wine @vasocellars , you can get some goodies on the side. We enjoyed the appetizers and then ordered some drinks. I swear they make the best cocktails in Japantown. We got the Cool as a Kyuuri with gin and cucumber, this was so refreshing, The Boss Lady, I like how this kinda tasted like cherries, and the passion totem which has a delicious passionfruit taste. Finally, came all the mains. We got the braised pork belly, this was so tender, uni pasta, which was made with squid ink for that dark look, and then another pasta with shrimp. One of the owners surprised us with a lychee martini with real lychee and you really don’t taste the alcohol. It was that good. 

Then, we made our way over to @amctheatres Kabuki to watch the advanced screening of @challengersmovie and if you like love triangles and tennis, it is a must watch. Finally, we ended with karaoke over at Dimples. We got some drinks, sang our heart out to Backstreet Boys, and that’s how we spent a night out in Japantown. 

📍 1700A Post St, San Francisco, CA 94115

Discover the hidden gem of Rancho Cordova, where adventure awaits amidst lush landscapes, tantalizing cuisines, and unique events. 

Nestled in the heart of California's Gold Country, this vibrant town offers endless exploration opportunities. The refreshing American River is ready to explore, with miles of trails and countless ways to get on the water. 

Indulge your senses with craft breweries and wine tasting in the renowned Barrel District. From offbeat attractions to year-round events, Rancho Cordova promises excitement at every turn.

What are you waiting for? Dive into the charm of Rancho Cordova today! Click the 🔗 in our bio to start your adventure.

caption:
Happy Earth Day from San Francisco! 🌎

📸 @fitzsimonsphotography

Every visitor knows San Francisco's scenic landscape sets it apart from many other urban destinations. However, our environment is delicate, and SF continues to do its part to protect it for future generations. 

From our extensive public transit system, pioneering farm-to-table culinary scene, and iconic green spaces, SF has set the standard for sustainable tourism.

Take a moment today to appreciate the wonders of nature around us and commit to making positive changes for a greener, more sustainable future. 

Together, we can make a difference!

caption:
This is everything I did in @coachella Day 1. We started with breakfast at the hotel before heading straight to Indio. Parking was super easy and we entered from the VIP entrance so there was no wait. Walking in, I was blown away with all the activations. Anyway, we booked our way to the Ferris Wheel to catch the views while the sun was still up. Then, we took some pictures. Actually, a lot of pictures. But it was so hot, so we didn’t last long and had to take a break. Pro tip: take advantage of all the hydration stations and sunblock stations.

The first artist we saw was @cloonee at the Shara stage. He kicked off day 1 strong. High energy all around. Then, we took a break at the @itsbennyblanco x @postmates Sauce Bar before going to go watch @sabrinacarpenter at the Coachella Stage. I’ve always seen her on TikTok, but she was amazing live. The dances, cinematography, and overall looks were so good. Of course we needed another photo op moment and then went to the central market where we ran into one of our friends from SF. 

I was starving, so we got some food from one of our SF faves, @thaifarmhouse . These were the volcano cup noodles that we got loaded with tofu, fried chicken, and tiger prawns. Next, we went to watch @bizarrap at the Sahara stage and if you like Latin trap and hip hop, this is the guy to see. People went crazy as the night went on. We stayed at the same stage to get a better spot to watch @peggygou_ . It was just so fun watching her dance crew perform to her set. It did get a bit cold at night, so we took a fun bike ride down to the shuttles to head back to our hotel and that was day 1. 

#coachella #coachella2024 #coachellaweekend2
#goldenvoice #goldenvoicebayarea #sfinfluencer

caption:
This is everything I did in @coachella Day 0. I am a last minute packer, but I made sure to bring my portable chargers, electric handheld fan, masks, ear plugs, sunscreen, you name it. I also got some energy chews and hydration powders from @skratchlabs so I’m set for the weekend. My friends picked me up in SF and surprised me with coffee and clase azul before we went to Palm Springs. The views driving down were gorgeous. We left at 10:30am and arrived in Pasadena by 4:30pm, so we made great time and there was barely any traffic. 

My other friends surprised me by preordering some birthday cupcakes from @susiecakesbakery that we picked up and then we drove a couple blocks over to @innout for a birthday dinner in the car. Honestly it was simple and perfect. Then, I knocked out and woke up 3 hours later in Palm Springs. I met up with the rest of the crew and we checked into our rooms at the @hiltonpalmsprings . We had a fun little photo-op that everyone set up for us and then went to Indian Wells for roll call. There was no line and it was so easy to get our wristbands. We went back to our hotel, and I took a nice shower to get all the sweat off and that was Day 0. 

#coachella #coachella2024 #coachellaweekend2

caption:
Today’s my birthday and it’s also the @sanfranciscospca ‘s birthday. I’m turning 29, and they’re turning 156 years old. I never knew they were around for that long, and I love coming here to play with the shelter dogs and cats. They even have puppies and kittens sometimes. If you love animals and want to volunteer with them, they have a location in SoMa, or if you’d like do donate to them for their Giving Day today, you can do that too. I love how this non profit creates miracles for animals in need. It was pretty fun to walk through to see all the animals, and I have a few friends that actually adopted from this exact SPCA. It’s such a cool spot. You gotta check it out! 

📍250 Florida St, San Francisco, CA 94103

alt: Photo shared by Andrew De Los Santos on April 21, 2024 tagging @coachella, @goldenvoice, and @goldenvoicebayarea. May be an image of 12 people and Stone Henge.
caption:
This is everything I did in @coachella Day 2. We went to the official pool party at @thepalmspringssurfclub @gvsurfclub and it was so chill. We hopped into the lazy river and just had a fun time floating down and enjoying the sun. They even have a slide and a wave pool that you can buy tickets to on the side. Then, our friends dropped us off at the shuttle and we made our way to the festival. 

The first thing we did was to find the speakeasy with the white fence. There’s a riddle you have to solve to enter, and once you’re inside, it’s like a private little tiki bar! There’s actually a second speakeasy inside this one and it has AC and a fun multi color dance floor. It’s perfect for taking a break. Next, we headed to @thaifarmhouse at the Central Market for a coconut water break. I met a cool artist @sandoner @sandonerart that was painting live, did an interview with @misslers from @marvelouscreators , and then we made our way to @sublime at the Coachella stage. 

He sang Santeria live and it was beautiful. We stopped to take some photos and then went to watch @icespice at the Sahara stage. She freaking killed it!! She was singing, twerking, and hyping up the audience. It was so packed that the walk out was a little bit nerve wrecking, but we made it out safe and sound. 

Finally, we bolted back to the Coachella Stage to watch @nodoubt . @gwenstefani was so cool to see live! She really knows how to perform for an audience. We heard some fun throwbacks and enjoyed our last set of the night. We wanted to beat the traffic out of Coachella, so we took the car back to our hotel and that was Day 2. 

#coachella #coachella2024 #coachellaweekend2
#goldenvoice #goldenvoicebayarea #sfinfluencer #sffoodie

🎵 NEXT WEEK — SF Live Presents Tony Lindsay & Friends feat. Bill Ortiz!

🎺 The sound of horns will fill the square as we spend the afternoon of moving & grooving with Tony and Bill— we’re electrifying the plaza! 

💃🏼 Grab your partner and your favorite pair of dancing shoes— we’ll see you next week!

— 

🏆 Tony Lindsay: After 25 years as the lead vocalist for Santana, Tony Lindsay has garnered 11 Grammy awards, traveled on several world tours and recorded on seven CDs: Milagro (1992), Supernatural (1999), Shaman (2002), Ceremony (2003) and Food for Thought (2004), Ultimate Santana (2007) and Multi-Dimensional Warrior (2008). He has also become a regular performer for The Golden State Warriors(NBA), The Santa Cruz Warriors (G league NBA), The San Francisco 49ers, The San Francisco Giants and The San Jose Sharks, singing The National Anthem. 

🎼 Bill Ortiz: The sweet, full tone and clear, assertive attack of Bill Ortiz has made him one of the most in-demand trumpet players of the Bay Area music scene for the past four decades. As a consummate trumpet player, Bill has spent many years playing music with some of the top artists from around the globe. In addition to becoming a member of the Santana Band in 2000, Bill’s performing/recording credits include work with such diverse and dynamic artists as Tito Puente, Destiny’s Child, Tony Toni Tone, Cachao, Herbie Hancock and more.

caption:
This is everything I did in @coachella Day 2. We went to the official pool party at @thepalmspringssurfclub @gvsurfclub and it was so chill. We hopped into the lazy river and just had a fun time floating down and enjoying the sun. They even have a slide and a wave pool that you can buy tickets to on the side. Then, our friends dropped us off at the shuttle and we made our way to the festival. 

The first thing we did was to find the speakeasy with the white fence. There’s a riddle you have to solve to enter, and once you’re inside, it’s like a private little tiki bar! There’s actually a second speakeasy inside this one and it has AC and a fun multi color dance floor. It’s perfect for taking a break. Next, we headed to @thaifarmhouse at the Central Market for a coconut water break. I met a cool artist @sandoner @sandonerart that was painting live, did an interview with @misslers from @marvelouscreators , and then we made our way to @sublime at the Coachella stage. 

He sang Santeria live and it was beautiful. We stopped to take some photos and then went to watch @icespice at the Sahara stage. She freaking killed it!! She was singing, twerking, and hyping up the audience. It was so packed that the walk out was a little bit nerve wrecking, but we made it out safe and sound. 

Finally, we bolted back to the Coachella Stage to watch @nodoubt . @gwenstefani was so cool to see live! She really knows how to perform for an audience. We heard some fun throwbacks and enjoyed our last set of the night. We wanted to beat the traffic out of Coachella, so we took the car back to our hotel and that was Day 2. 

#coachella #coachella2024 #coachellaweekend2
#goldenvoice #goldenvoicebayarea #sfinfluencer #sffoodie

⚡️ SAN FRANCISCO— ARE YOU READY FOR SF LIVE?

🌻 @GreatNorthernSF, @MonarchSF, and @IlluminateTheArts presents ELECTRIC FIELDS on Saturday, May 4th at the ICONIC Golden Gate Park Bandshell!

☀️ Kickstart a summer of music, catch some rays and #BeHearNow — courtesy of a lineup headlined by @DocMartinLA, @GalenSunset, @DJM3SF, with Lyja + &ndmore on Support 

🌐 ALL ARE WELCOME — FREE & OUTDOORS! 

📲 Tap in to our bio for more!

— 

✨@DocMartinLA  has earned the respect of many who are fanatic about his style of DJ’ ing. His style crosses over from all timeless genres providing his listeners a new outlook & ever growing futuristic, unique sound. He can always surprise you with a rare classic that crosses time zones and still hits the spot even now.

✨ Inspired by the DIY parties of the UK and reggae soundsystem culture, @GalenSunset founded Sunset Sound System by setting up a generator and speakers at a park in Berkeley, California every Sunday to spin records for free!

✨ @DJM3SF has staked his everlasting claim in the Bay Area music community in 1990 as a key promoter and DJ, roles for which he took on the abbreviated appellation of M3, short for “Makes Me Move”. Begun as a fluid, down-tempo approach, M3 eventually evolved his sound to the expression of Deep House , Disco and Tech House chuggers he is known for today.

—

caption:
Did you know there is a giant Camera Obscura in San Francisco? 📷@karstenkoehn

Unfamiliar with a camera obscura? It's a fascinating device that projects an image of the surroundings onto a surface using only natural light sources, typically sunlight.

There have been many different versions here at the Cliff House. However, this one was installed in 1946 and has been continuously operated ever since.  The Camera Obscura was even added to the National Register of Historic Places in 2001! 

Check it out next time you are around the historic Cliff House (scheduled to reopen in late 2024).

Learn more about the Camera Obscura and how to visit at the 🔗 in our bio.

caption:
🔊 WE ARE SF LIVE 🔊

🌉And we’re here to amplify all the love and power that is San Francisco’s music legacy.

🎟️Over the next six months, we’re creating stages for San Francisco music to shine — all in some of the most iconic outdoor locations like Golden Gate Park’s Bandshell, Union Square, Civic Center Plaza, and so much more!

🌐 SF Live shows are all FREE, FAMILY FRIENDLY, and a chance to get outdoors and enjoy an SF summer! Most importantly— we’ve got a diverse lineup that is sure to have somethin’ for everyone!

📲 Stay connected with us at @SFLiveFest & you won’t miss a beat! See you at the show — #BeHearNow!

••

Supported by Mayor London N. Breed and the San Francisco Office of Economic and Workforce Development, SF Live is one of several initiatives to support the local nightlife and entertainment sector, alongside fee waivers, permit streamlining, and other efforts to support the sector’s recovery. SF Live is supported through a $2.5 million investment from the California State Legislature that was led by City Attorney David Chiu when he was an Assemblymember.

alt: Photo by The best things to do in San Francisco on April 10, 2024. May be an image of skyscraper, buildings, bridge and text.
caption:
Save this Mission Bay neighborhood itinerary:

Morning:
Start your day with breakfast at @peasantpies, where you can indulge in sweet and savor pies to fuel your adventures. Try the classic Egg, Sausage, and Potato Pie or the delicious Lentil and Yam pie. Don't forget the coffee! 

After breakfast, head to @stagecoachgreens for SF-themed mini-golf fun! Challenge your friends to a round of mini-golf among quirky and iconic San Francisco landmarks. Remember to grab drinks or snacks from @SparkSocialSF, one of SF's best food truck parks! 

Looking for more adventure? Venture to @dogpatchpaddle and explore the San Francisco Bay's historical sites, piers, and marine life on a kayak or paddle board. 

Afternoon:
For lunch, enjoy waterfront dining at @missionrock. Savor delicious dishes while taking in stunning views of the bay. Relax and unwind as you recharge for the rest of the day's adventure. 

After lunch, make your way to @cavana.sf, the rooftop lounge at the brand-new @lumahotelsanfrancisco. Sip on South American-inspired cocktails while enjoying the sunshine and San Francisco's skyline views!

Evening:
Catch the excitement of a @SFGiants game at @OraclePark! Cheer on the team while indulging in classic ballpark treats like Gilroy Garlic Fries and hot dogs.

Not into baseball? Check out a Warriors game or event at the state-of-the-art @chase_center. It's the perfect place to see your favorite artists or the iconic Warriors play!

Looking for a place to stay in the neighborhood? The Luma Hotel offers an artsy atmosphere and fantastic views of the surrounding area, making it the perfect spot for your evening in San Francisco.

caption:
🚨 ONLY SEVEN MORE DAYS TILL OUR FIRST EVER DFT! We’ve been so excited to share what we have in store for you! We’ll be spotlighting each of our entertainment zones — so keep in touch by following us at @DFTSanFrancisco!

MONTHLY PERFORMANCES CURATED BY:

💿 Inside @111minnagallery : @kalwradio will host conversations, music. 

🪩 Discoteca on Minna Street: @thegracetowers will host an outdoor street discoteca on Minna Street, featuring Bay Area Performers and DJs playing a wide range of music genres including disco, salsa, reggaeton, house y más! 

👑 The Art Car Stage @ (2nd at Howard st.) will start a certified @theoasissf party with drag, DJs, and more in the early evening and set the stage for special guest performers–brought to you by @themidwaysf and @apeconcerts to close out the night. 

💃🏼 @natomacabana Dance Hall (Outside Natoma Cabana on Natoma at 2nd Street) @ybgfestival and A LITTLE x will bring you live music to get down to. Grab your partner and head to the Dance Hall for salsa, funk, and more grooves to keep you moving in the streets. 

🎸 Jams on Jessie Street (Jessie Street at 2nd Street) Jessie Street comes alive with bands and live music brought to you by @NoisePop, plus some fun  surprises and wandering street performances.

🌐 Are we seeing you there?

—

🌉 FREE RSVP in our bio!

alt: Photo shared by Andrew De Los Santos on May 08, 2024 tagging @topofthemarksf, and @icmarkhopkins. May be an image of 1 person and bowler hat.
caption:
I’ve been going to @topofthemarksf for years, and they just celebrated their 85th Anniversary. Top of the Mark at the @icmarkhopkins in Nob HIll was so kind to invite me to their celebration yesterday. Michael, the general manager told us the story of how hotel opened back in 1926, nearly a century ago. The main stage was historically known to host live bands, so I was so happy we got to experience some of that. Props to @vintagejukeboxmusic . We got some champagne, light bites, and even got to customize our own old fashioned. I got mine made with strawberry rhubard and peach bitters. If you come here on an empty stomach, they do also have some delicious options on their menu, my favorite being one of the flatbreads to start, short rib sliders for the main, and a chocolate lava cake for dessert. Definitely come during sunset to catch golden hour. You gotta check it out! 

📍 999 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108
#sfinfluencer #sfblogger #sffoodie #sfrooftopbars #rooftopbar

Artist Highlight: @djumami 
.
🎶 🌻🎶We are so excited to welcome back @djumami as our special guest for the @bhangraandbeats 2024 season Kick Off. Bring your dancing shoes and come get down with us. 🎶🌻🎶
.
.
DJ Umami was born, raised, and is based in the Bay Area. She is currently a resident DJ for the
San Francisco Giants and was a Golden State Warriors DJ from 2012 - 2021. The unmistakable
flavor and fervor she brings to any dancefloor, celebration, or occasion, is how she splashed
onto the local scene in San Francisco in 2008. 

Within a year of rockin’ the turntables, she gained residency with the prestigiously talented female DJ crew “Peaches”. In 2015, she secured a weekly residency for the radio station Q102 FM, and was recently a resident DJ for KALW.

DJ Umami’s rise in the music industry has included opening sets for Dua Lipa, Anderson Paak,
Questlove, Outside Lands, SXSW, amongst others. She is frequently requested for corporate
parties, having worked with Meta, Google, Nike, and Women in Tech, to name a few; and is part
of the Creative Collective for Bacardí Ocho Reserve. 

While R&B, Soul, and Hip Hop are foundational to her musical taste, it’s Umami’s ability to read the energy of a crowd and belief in music as healing that allows her to serve an eclectic menu of sounds. 

As a Filipina American, she hopes to bring more visibility to the craft, and inspire the next generation of women DJs. 🎉🎶
.
.
.

Join us as we step into the future at CREATE! with a celebration of 3024! 🌟 

Embrace the transformative power of AI and its potential to unite and inspire innovation in San Francisco and beyond. DJ Cole Berggren from the Blue Bear School of Music (@bluebearmusic) will take us on an interactive musical journey, mixing both top hits and AI-generated songs from AI Artist Laura Gallmeyer’s special album for CREATE!, “Echoes of the Algorithm.” Get ready to dive into the music with hands-on mixing sessions using professional DJ equipment. 🎧🎶 

CREATE! is a visual and performing arts celebration of San Francisco’s creative past, present, and future happening on Landing at Leidesdorff, 200 Leidesdorff Street, on April 25th from 4-8 PM. The event is FREE to attend and open to the public. 🎨 RSVP and don’t miss out on this captivating experience! ✨🌉

caption:
Experience creativity in every stroke! 🎨✨ 

This digital masterpiece was painted live by artist Jeremy Sutton at CREATE!, a vibrant celebration of the arts held at Landing at Leidesdorff, next to the iconic Transamerica Pyramid. This free public event, nestled where San Francisco's financial district meets North Beach, Chinatown, and the old Barbary Coast, truly encapsulates the creative spirit of the city. Produced by The Downtown SF Partnership, the event took place in the picturesque, car-free Leidesdorff and Commercial Streets, providing a perfect backdrop for Jeremy’s art. The canvas featured the stunning “Beyond the Sea – The Life and Legacy of Captain Leidesdorff” mural by Twin Walls Mural Company, allowing visitors to watch the vibrant scene come to life in real time.

caption:
If you haven't heard of Landing at Leidesdorff, it's Downtown San Francisco's newest destination & on April 25th the Downtown SF Partnership is hosting CREATE! A Celebration of SF’s Artistic History — a *free*  outdoor, immersive visual & performing arts celebration — spotlighting San Francisco's creative past, present & future!

🎨 Located at the intersection of Commercial & Leidesdorff Streets, this fun activation will showcase a variety of local artists, performers & chefs to honor the artistic history of the downtown area, particularly those that resided in the Montgomery Block building also known as “Monkey Block.”

🍹 In addition to bites & mockatils from restaurants that include The Barrel Room, @wayfaretavern, @ozumorestaurants, & @sfsweetpotato — get ready for a ton of awesome programming.

🎶 This includes:
• on-demand poems by prolific poet, Silvi Alcivar
• live event painter Jeremy Sutton who will be creating a work of art as the event unfolds
• a DJ spinning tracks using a playlist sequence generated by AI
• all-female MoToR/dance percussive dance company redefining movement & so much more!

➡️ Comment CREATE! & I'll DM you all the info for this *free* Downtown San Francisco event & follow @cheycheyfromthebay for more San Francisco food, fun & recommendations!

📍San Francisco, California @landingatleidesdorff @sf_downtown

caption:
Good morning, San Francisco! 🌉 Every year, at 5:13 AM on April 18th, San Franciscans gather at the intersection of Market, Geary, and Kearny Streets at Lotta’s Fountain to commemorate the anniversary of the 1906 Earthquake and Fire. This morning, a large crowd of San Franciscans met up at the Lotta Crabtree Fountain to honor our city's incredible spirit of resilience. From the ashes of that day, San Franciscans have rebuilt and risen, stronger and more united. Here's to the indomitable spirit of San Franciscans—past, present, and future! 🌆
